{
  "texts": [
    "However, model generalization does not allow for a perfect fit to all data points (Fig. 4",
    "Next, we asked whether FCNET was simply overfitting a small subset of similar subjects.",
    "We calculated the z-score of each metric with respect to the 19 folds cross-validated subjects (see Methods).",
    "For all metrics, we found that ~65% of all z-scores lied in the ±σ range and ~95% fell in the ±2σ.",
    "Even more, when repeating the training with different starting weights, all subjects but 2 showed different scores (Fig. 5a); they were not uniquely classified as outliers and therefore were considered in all the subsequent analysis (p > 0.05, df = 17, two-tailed Grubbs test)."
  ]
}